did.abstract: The mission of the Academic Publications office is to edit university publications such as the University Bulletin. Materials for this collection include dissertation abstracts, commencement programs (including the Law and Medical School), class schedules, University Bulletins, degrees conferred, President Carroll inauguration, Law School centennial and special convocations, stylistic guidelines, and master course and program data forms. The material ranges in date from 1943 to 2004.

prefercite.p: Academic Publications Office records, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: Portions of this collection are unprocessed. Some records may be restricted.Please see Special Collections staff for assistance.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: These records were transferred to University Archives in 1998 and 2009.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Academic Publications reports to the office of Graduate Studies and Academic Affairs, which is a part of the Executive Vice President for Academic Affairs office. The mission of this office is to edit university publications such as the university bulletin.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials for this collection include dissertation abstracts, commencement programs (including the Law and Medical School, class schedules, University Bulletins, degrees conferred, President Carroll inauguration, Law School centennial and special convocations, stylistic guidelines, master course and program data forms, Middle States, GWSolutions, and second-class postage permit filings. The material ranges in date from 1943 to 2004.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into three series. They include Publications, Stylistic guidelines, and Master Course and Program Data Forms.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of dissertation abstracts, commencement programs (including the Law and Medical School, class schedules, University Bulletins, degrees conferred, President Carroll inauguration, Law School centennial and special convocations. The material ranges in date from 1943-97. They were transferred to University Archives in 1998.

scopecontent.p: This series contains files pertaining to the Master Course and Program Data Forms for the Columbian College of Arts and Sciences and for the School of Medicine and Health Sciences.
